      "timestamp": "2026-04-16T00:00:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "MagicMock(spec=AppConfig) returns truthy mock for new bool fields, causing task_negotiation_enabled to evaluate True and trigger negotiation step unexpectedly",
      "file": "tests/unit/test_workflow_modes.py",
      "root_cause": "When a new bool attribute is added to AppConfig, MagicMock(spec=AppConfig) serves a truthy MagicMock for that attribute instead of the default False. Any code guarded by getattr(config, 'new_bool_field', False) will be bypassed because the mock attribute is truthy.",
      "fix": "Added `cfg.task_negotiation_enabled = False` to the config fixture in test_workflow_modes.py. Rule: every new bool field added to AppConfig must also be explicitly set to its default in any MagicMock(spec=AppConfig) fixture that exercises code guarded by that field.",
      "tags": [
        "test",
        "mock",
        "appconfig",
        "boolean-default"
